      <prefercite id="aspace_f02abbbf9c428ea67e7becda71c435e0">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Silvain van Praet Papers (MS 1241). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_e1e83b7850e473555f59c8f1e1c64fcc">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Silvain van Praet was a member of the city government in Ostend, Belgium. He kept a diary during the 1914-1918 German occupation of the city.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d3b20fc45ef47944ed32ae281037eda7">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Principally a manuscript diary kept in English in twelve school notebooks by Silvain van Praet, a member of the Ostend (Belgium) city government, from the day of the German occupation of Ostend (1914 October 14) until its liberation (1918 October 17). It was concealed in a hole in the wall of the Maison Communal. There is also a typescript copy of the manuscript (568 p.) and several related documents.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_aec2c23cc3718e0e357cfd2a898ca042" localtype="UseSurrogate">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm. Patrons must use HM 229 instead of the originals.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
  
